3408 - <p><b>Serum 207</b> is a temporary cure for the <a href="/wiki/Afflicted" title="Afflicted">afflicted</a> villagers of <a href="/wiki/Mort%27ton" title="Mort'ton">Mort'ton</a> who are otherwise incoherent. A player who has read the <a href="/wiki/Diary_of_Herbi_Flax" title="Diary of Herbi Flax" class="mw-redirect">Diary of Herbi Flax</a> during the quest <a href="/wiki/Shades_of_Mort%27ton" title="Shades of Mort'ton">Shades of Mort'ton</a> and has a <a href="/wiki/Herblore" title="Herblore">Herblore</a> level of at least 15 may produce it by adding <a href="/wiki/Clean_tarromin" title="Clean tarromin">Clean tarromin</a> to a <a href="/wiki/Vial_of_water" title="Vial of water">vial of water</a> and then adding <a href="/wiki/Ashes" title="Ashes">Ashes</a> giving 50 herblore <a href="/wiki/Experience" title="Experience">experience</a>. - <p><b>Serum 207</b> is a temporary cure for the <a href="/wiki/Afflicted" title="Afflicted">afflicted</a> villagers of <a href="/wiki/Mort%27ton" title="Mort'ton">Mort'ton</a> who are otherwise incoherent. A player who has read the <a href="/wiki/Diary_of_Herbi_Flax" title="Diary of Herbi Flax" class="mw-redirect">Diary of Herbi Flax</a> during the quest <a href="/wiki/Shades_of_Mort%27ton" title="Shades of Mort'ton">Shades of Mort'ton</a> and has a <a href="/wiki/Herblore" title="Herblore">Herblore</a> level of at least 15 may produce it by adding <a href="/wiki/Clean_tarromin" title="Clean tarromin">Clean tarromin</a> to a <a href="/wiki/Vial_of_water" title="Vial of water">vial of water</a> and then adding <a href="/wiki/Ashes" title="Ashes">Ashes</a> giving 50 herblore <a href="/wiki/Experience" title="Experience">experience</a>.

3416 - <p><b>Serum 208</b> is a permanent cure for the <a href="/wiki/Afflicted" title="Afflicted">afflicted</a> villagers of <a href="/wiki/Mort%27ton" title="Mort'ton">Mort'ton</a>. It is used during the <a href="/wiki/Shades_of_Mort%27ton" title="Shades of Mort'ton">Shades of Mort'ton</a> quest to turn Afflicted NPCs back into normal characters so the player can interact with them. It is made by using <a href="/wiki/Serum_207" title="Serum 207">Serum 207</a> on the sacred flame at the rebuilt temple. - <p><b>Serum 208</b> is a permanent cure for the <a href="/wiki/Afflicted" title="Afflicted">afflicted</a> villagers of <a href="/wiki/Mort%27ton" title="Mort'ton">Mort'ton</a>. 4749 - <p><b>Torag's platebody</b> is <a href="/wiki/Armour#Melee_armour" title="Armour">melee armour</a> worn in the <a href="/wiki/Inventory#body_Slot" title="Inventory">body slot</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Torag_the_Corrupted%27s_equipment" title="Torag the Corrupted's equipment">Torag The Corrupted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wear Torag's platebody a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. Torag's platebody is also one of the strongest platebodies in RuneScape but it has the downside of degrading after 10 hours. When clicking "check" on the platebody it will show you its charges left. When it has fully degraded it turns to a broken torag's platebody.  - <p><b>Torag's platebody</b> is <a href="/wiki/Armour#Melee_armour" title="Armour">melee armour</a> worn in the <a href="/wiki/Inventory#body_Slot" title="Inventory">body slot</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Torag_the_Corrupted%27s_equipment" title="Torag the Corrupted's equipment">Torag The Corrupted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wear Torag's platebody a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. Torag's platebody is also one of the strongest platebodies in RuneScape but it has the downside of degrading after 10 hours. When clicking "check" on the platebody it will show you its charges left. When it has fully degraded it turns to a broken torag's platebody.

4914 - <p><b>Guthan's warspear</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Weapons#Member_melee_weapons" title="Weapons" class="mw-redirect">melee weapon</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Guthan_the_Infested%27s_equipment" title="Guthan the Infested's equipment">Guthan The Infested's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. Guthan's warspear is a two handed weapon and requires 70 <a href="/wiki/Attack" title="Attack">Attack</a> to wield. This weapon <b>cannot</b> be made using the <a href="/wiki/Smithing" title="Smithing">Smithing</a> <a href="/wiki/Skill" title="Skill" class="mw-redirect">skill</a>. - <p><b>Guthan's warspear</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Weapons#Member_melee_weapons" title="Weapons" class="mw-redirect">melee weapon</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Guthan_the_Infested%27s_equipment" title="Guthan the Infested's equipment">Guthan The Infested's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. Guthan's warspear is a two handed weapon and requires 70 <a href="/wiki/Attack" title="Attack">Attack</a> to wield. This weapon <b>cannot</b> be made using the <a href="/wiki/Smithing" title="Smithing">Smithing</a> <a href="/wiki/Skill" title="Skill" class="mw-redirect">skill</a>.

4920 - <p><b>Guthan's platebody</b> is <a href="/wiki/Armour#Melee_armour" title="Armour">melee armour</a> worn in the <a href="/wiki/Inventory#Body_Slot" title="Inventory">body slot</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Guthan_the_Infested%27s_equipment" title="Guthan the Infested's equipment">Guthan The Infested's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wear Guthan's platebody a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. It is currently tied with <a href="/wiki/Torag%27s_platebody" title="Torag's platebody">Torag's platebody</a> and <a href="/wiki/Dharok%27s_platebody" title="Dharok's platebody">Dharok's platebody</a> as being the third strongest platebody in the game behind <a href="/wiki/Statius%27s_platebody" title="Statius's platebody">Statius's platebody</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Torva_platebody" title="Torva platebody">Torva platebody</a>. - <p><b>Guthan's platebody</b> is <a href="/wiki/Armour#Melee_armour" title="Armour">melee armour</a> worn in the <a href="/wiki/Inventory#Body_Slot" title="Inventory">body slot</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Guthan_the_Infested%27s_equipment" title="Guthan the Infested's equipment">Guthan The Infested's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wear Guthan's platebody a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. It is currently tied with <a href="/wiki/Torag%27s_platebody" title="Torag's platebody">Torag's platebody</a> and <a href="/wiki/Dharok%27s_platebody" title="Dharok's platebody">Dharok's platebody</a> as being the third strongest platebody in the game behind <a href="/wiki/Statius%27s_platebody" title="Statius's platebody">Statius's platebody</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Torva_platebody" title="Torva platebody">Torva platebody</a>.

4938 - <p><b>Karil's crossbow</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Two-handed_crossbow" title="Two-handed crossbow">Two-handed crossbow</a> <a href="/wiki/Weapons#Member_ranged_weapons" title="Weapons" class="mw-redirect">ranged weapon</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Karil_the_Tainted%27s_equipment" title="Karil the Tainted's equipment">Karil the Tainted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wield the crossbow players require a <a href="/wiki/Ranged" title="Ranged">Ranged</a> level of 70. It requires ammunition called <a href="/wiki/Bolt_rack" title="Bolt rack">bolt racks</a>. Both the Karil's crossbow and Karil's pistol crossbow are the only crossbows to use bolt racks. - <p><b>Karil's crossbow</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Two-handed_crossbow" title="Two-handed crossbow">Two-handed crossbow</a> <a href="/wiki/Weapons#Member_ranged_weapons" title="Weapons" class="mw-redirect">ranged weapon</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Karil_the_Tainted%27s_equipment" title="Karil the Tainted's equipment">Karil the Tainted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wield the crossbow players require a <a href="/wiki/Ranged" title="Ranged">Ranged</a> level of 70. It requires ammunition called <a href="/wiki/Bolt_rack" title="Bolt rack">bolt racks</a>. Both the Karil's crossbow and Karil's pistol crossbow are the only crossbows to use bolt racks.

4958 - <p><b>Torag's hammer</b> is a 2-handed <a href="/wiki/Weapons#Member_two-handed_melee_weapons" title="Weapons" class="mw-redirect">melee weapon</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Torag_the_Corrupted%27s_equipment" title="Torag the Corrupted's equipment">Torag the Corrupted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. 4968 - <p><b>Torag's platebody</b> is <a href="/wiki/Armour#Melee_armour" title="Armour">melee armour</a> worn in the <a href="/wiki/Inventory#body_Slot" title="Inventory">body slot</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Torag_the_Corrupted%27s_equipment" title="Torag the Corrupted's equipment">Torag The Corrupted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wear Torag's platebody a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. Torag's platebody is also one of the strongest platebodies in RuneScape but it has the downside of degrading after 10 hours. When clicking "check" on the platebody it will show you its charges left. When it has fully degraded it turns to a broken torag's platebody.  - <p><b>Torag's platebody</b> is <a href="/wiki/Armour#Melee_armour" title="Armour">melee armour</a> worn in the <a href="/wiki/Inventory#body_Slot" title="Inventory">body slot</a> that is part of <a href="/wiki/Torag_the_Corrupted%27s_equipment" title="Torag the Corrupted's equipment">Torag The Corrupted's set</a> of <a href="/wiki/Barrows_equipment" title="Barrows equipment">barrows equipment</a>. To wear Torag's platebody a player must have 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a>. Torag's platebody is also one of the strongest platebodies in RuneScape but it has the downside of degrading after 10 hours. When clicking "check" on the platebody it will show you its charges left. When it has fully degraded it turns to a broken torag's platebody.

It requires level 70 <a href="/wiki/Defence" title="Defence">Defence</a> to wear.

10909 - <p><b>Mixture - step 1</b> is created by adding <a href="/wiki/Unicorn_horn_dust" title="Unicorn horn dust">unicorn horn dust</a> to <a href="/wiki/Super_restore_potion" title="Super restore potion" class="mw-redirect">Super restore potions</a>. <a href="/wiki/Clean_snake_weed" title="Clean snake weed">Clean snake weed</a> and <a href="/wiki/Nail_beast_nails" title="Nail beast nails">nail beast nails</a> can be added to make this potion into <a href="/wiki/Sanfew_serum" title="Sanfew serum">Sanfew serum</a>. After <a href="/wiki/Clean_snake_weed" title="Clean snake weed">snake weed</a> is added the potion becomes <a href="/wiki/Mixture_-_step_2" title="Mixture - step 2">Mixture - step 2</a>. - <p><b>Mixture - step 1</b> is created by adding <a href="/wiki/Unicorn_horn_dust" title="Unicorn horn dust">unicorn horn dust</a> to <a href="/wiki/Super_restore_potion" title="Super restore potion" class="mw-redirect">Super restore potions</a>. <a href="/wiki/Clean_snake_weed" title="Clean snake weed">Clean snake weed</a> and <a href="/wiki/Nail_beast_nails" title="Nail beast nails">nail beast nails</a> can be added to make this potion into <a href="/wiki/Sanfew_serum" title="Sanfew serum">Sanfew serum</a>. After <a href="/wiki/Clean_snake_weed" title="Clean snake weed">snake weed</a> is added the potion becomes <a href="/wiki/Mixture_-_step_2" title="Mixture - step 2">Mixture - step 2</a>.

11501 - <div class="floatleft"><a href="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/c/c6/Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png/revision/latest?cb=20140109005915" 	class="image image-thumbnail" 	 	 	><img src="data:image/gif;base64R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" 	 alt="Antidote+ mix detail" 	class="lzy lzyPlcHld " 	 	data-image-key="Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Antidote+ mix detail.png" 	 data-src="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/c/c6/Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/50?cb=20140109005915" 	 width="50" 	 height="80" 	 	 	 onload="if(typeof ImgLzy=== #39;object #39;){ImgLzy.load(this)}" 	><noscript><img src="http://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/runescape2/images/c/c6/Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/50?cb=20140109005915" 	 alt="Antidote+ mix detail" 	class="" 	 	data-image-key="Antidote%2B_mix_detail.png" 	data-image-name="Antidote+ mix detail.png" 	 	 width="50" 	 height="80" 	 	 	 	></noscript></a></div>An <b>Antidote+ mix</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Barbarian_Potions#Barbarian_potions" title="Barbarian Potions" class="mw-redirect">Barbarian potion</a> that cures poison status and gives poison immunity for 9 minutes as well as healing 600 <a href="/wiki/Life_points" title="Life points">life points</a> per dose. It is made by using <a href="/wiki/Caviar" title="Caviar">Caviar</a> on a <a href="/wiki/Antipoison%2B_(2)" title="Antipoison+ (2)" class="mw-redirect">Antipoison+ (2)</a>. It requires a <a href="/wiki/Herblore" title="Herblore">Herblore</a> level of 74 to make and gives 52 experience. This mix can only be created after completing the Herblore part of <a href="/wiki/Barbarian_training" title="Barbarian training" class="mw-redirect">Barbarian training</a> with <a href="/wiki/Otto_Godblessed" title="Otto Godblessed">Otto Godblessed</a>. It is obtained by killing <a href="/wiki/Revenants" title="Revenants">Revenants</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Forinthry_Dungeon" title="Forinthry Dungeon">Forinthry Dungeon</a> or the <a href="/wiki/Chaos_Elemental" title="Chaos Elemental">Chaos Elemental</a> in very deep <a href="/wiki/Wilderness" title="Wilderness">Wilderness</a> and is considered the best drop possible from said foes. This piece of weaponry was released with the release of PvP worlds on <a href="/wiki/15_October" title="15 October">15 October</a> <a href="/wiki/2008" title="2008">2008</a>. - <p><b>Vesta's longsword</b> is the fourth strongest longsword in the game beaten only by the <a href="/wiki/Chaotic_longsword" title="Chaotic longsword">chaotic longsword</a> <a href="/wiki/Drygore_longsword" title="Drygore longsword">drygore longsword</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Tetsu_katana" title="Tetsu katana">tetsu katana</a>. 14103 - <p>The <b>volatile fletching knife</b> is created by operating the <a href="/wiki/Volatile_clay_tool" title="Volatile clay tool">volatile clay tool</a>. It is used in the <a href="/wiki/Fletching" title="Fletching">Fletching</a> skill and gives 29340 <a href="/wiki/Bonus_experience" title="Bonus experience">bonus experience</a>. It is obtained through the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> minigame and costs 20 Stealing Creation points to purchase. Once the bonus experience is gained it is not necessary to carry the discharged tools around to benefit from it. The tool will lose 10% of its potential bonus experience if you revert it. If you attempt to revert it when it is depleted it will be destroyed.  - <p>The <b>volatile fletching knife</b> is created by operating the <a href="/wiki/Volatile_clay_tool" title="Volatile clay tool">volatile clay tool</a>. It is used in the <a href="/wiki/Fletching" title="Fletching">Fletching</a> skill and gives 29340 <a href="/wiki/Bonus_experience" title="Bonus experience">bonus experience</a>. It is obtained through the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> minigame and costs 20 Stealing Creation points to purchase. Once the bonus experience is gained it is not necessary to carry the discharged tools around to benefit from it. The tool will lose 10% of its potential bonus experience if you revert it. If you attempt to revert it when it is depleted it will be destroyed. 
14104 - 0 coins - 0 coins
14105 - <p>A <b>volatile clay needle</b> is one of the possible tools that the <a href="/wiki/Volatile_Tool" title="Volatile Tool" class="mw-redirect">Volatile Tool</a> can transform into. The needle gives  29340 <a href="/wiki/Bonus_experience" title="Bonus experience">bonus experience</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Crafting" title="Crafting">Crafting</a> skill and it can be obtained by chance in the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> <a href="/wiki/Minigame" title="Minigame" class="mw-redirect">minigame</a> by purchasing the <a href="/wiki/Volatile_Tool" title="Volatile Tool" class="mw-redirect">Volatile Tool</a> for 20 stealing creation points and making it transform. Once the bonus experience is gained it is not necessary to carry the discharged tools around to benefit from it. The tool will lose 10% of its potential bonus experience if you revert it. If you attempt to revert it when it is depleted it will be destroyed.  - <p>A <b>volatile clay needle</b> is one of the possible tools that the <a href="/wiki/Volatile_Tool" title="Volatile Tool" class="mw-redirect">Volatile Tool</a> can transform into. The needle gives  29340 <a href="/wiki/Bonus_experience" title="Bonus experience">bonus experience</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Crafting" title="Crafting">Crafting</a> skill and it can be obtained by chance in the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> <a href="/wiki/Minigame" title="Minigame" class="mw-redirect">minigame</a> by purchasing the <a href="/wiki/Volatile_Tool" title="Volatile Tool" class="mw-redirect">Volatile Tool</a> for 20 stealing creation points and making it transform. Once the bonus experience is gained it is not necessary to carry the discharged tools around to benefit from it. The tool will lose 10% of its potential bonus experience if you revert it. If you attempt to revert it when it is depleted it will be destroyed.

14115 - <p>The <b>sacred clay robe bottom</b> is a reward from the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> minigame. The sacred clay robe bottom gives 24450 bonus experience in the <a href="/wiki/Magic" title="Magic">Magic</a> skill. It may be recharged by spending 20 Stealing Creation points at the sacred clay reward mystic. - <p>The <b>sacred clay robe bottom</b> is a reward from the <a href="/wiki/Stealing_Creation" title="Stealing Creation">Stealing Creation</a> minigame.
